column2: Lots of rain lately but none today or yesterday.
Cloudy-rainy.  Last one we will be able to do this year.
No rain lately + water level down a little.
Stuff floating on water-from trees- etc.  Some algae along shores.
Rained last night.  Algae in water.
Had rain for couple days before today.
Water level remains higher than past few years.
Water level remains high.  Rains continue-none today.
Two days ago there was a hard rain.
Previous two days have been very windy.
There has been a lot of rain over last few days and it was quite windy today.
Lots of rain and wind lately.
A lot of rain the last couple of days.
Lots of wind and rain the day before.
Cloudy- calm- night before had rain- chem training
Partly cloudy.  Choppy water.  Bottom temp 43.5 F- Bottom D.O. 2 mg/l.
It was a cloudy- misty cold day with no wind.
Clear- light wind- leaves beginning to turn
sunny day- warm- light variable winds
sunny with a few clouds- light chop-north winds

71 degrees- sunny- south/southwest winds 12 mph- choppy waters.  Because of the wind and choppy waters- tried real hard to make sure temp probe was at right depths.  Decided to do this on July 20th since the satellite was going over today.
Partly cloudy with light west winds with some gusts- mild chop on water. Air temp around 70 degrees
mostly sunny- 70 degrees out- light variable winds
sunny and clear- calm to light breeze from the west.
mostly sunny- 78 degrees-  winds 0 to 5. over two weeks of warm weather- no rain. murky water except over in Portage Bay (by 27S) where for some reason it is pretty clear.

partly cloudy- 37 degrees- n/nw wind 4mp. a couple of weeks ago- we spotted some blue/green algae in a couple of bays. We finally got about 3 inches of rain over last week end and beginning of this week.
sunny skies- calm  winds 0 to 5 from the southeast.  water looks clear except for pollen so I gave it a 2 in perception because of pollen.

First chance to get back out on the lake in June for testing as the rains came in and if not raining- very windy or very overcast. Today partly sunny- calm winds. Haven't seen any baby ducks other than one family of geese.  Our wood duck nest failed this year. No sign of any activity for two weeks and then saw a mink go into the box so we went to check it out and found the nest abandon probably due too either too many merganser eggs dropped in (6) and only 3 wood duck eggs or the cracked open egg rotting full of bugs that was in the nest...   Haven't seen any baby loons or nesting of the loons in our bay. Normally a pair always nest in our bay but with the low water levels....the normal area is not a good spot any more.
mostly sunny- slight breeze.. finally have a family of baby mallard ducks (7 babies) swimming around. Eagle tried to attack but was not successful. Have not seen any loon chicks.
Partly cloudy- hazy sunshine. calm winds. 77 degrees
partly cloudy- about 10 mile an hour winds
67 degrees- 5 mile winds from the W/NW- sunny. Last Thursday (12th) we started to get a blue/green algae bloom. Heavy rains came that night and knocked the algae down.
71 degrees out- light variable winds. sunny skies.
mostly cloudy- 64 degrees. variable winds. got out to take temps after a little rain storm passed.  water color sort of a blue/ green
Due to bad weather and timing- this is my first testing of the season. Partly  cloudy- 66 degrees- lite breeze.
Hot- humid- partly cloudy... winds calm.. had a bad storm the night before. Over 2 inches of rain and lots of wind and lightning.
mostly sunny- light breeze- some gusts.  Water was not quite clear but not quite murky either.... mid 70's
Sunny and warm- west winds 5 to 10. Had 3/4 of an inch of rain last night.
clear + sunny. winds variable around 5 mph from the south. spotted the 2 young eagles.
Hazy sunshine- light winds. Had 2 inches of rain on 6/14 along with high winds. Found some surface algae in some bays.
Beautiful sunny clear day. 70 degrees  light breeze
mostly sunny- winds about 5 miles from the N/NW gorgeous day!!
Winds 5 to 10 W NW - sunny and hot

beautiful sunny morning- very light breeze. Lake is looking really green. Water is about 8 inches lower than in June. Friend mentioned the bay by Hwy 27 was clear but when you got to the main lake you could see the green color start.
sunny and clear. west winds about 5 mph. lack of rain. water level continues to drop and lake is very green.
sunny light wind  38 degrees in town last night. water is still green looking but getter a little better.

column1: very slight amount of pollen on top of water

column2: partly cloudy- mild to moderdate chop. HOT
Partly cloudy- calm to slight breeze.  Saw mama deer and her twin fawns drinking water off the point.
Clear sunny skies- 2 loons making calls.  Last 2 nights in the high 30's in town.
Same two loons hanging around. Calm winds- partly cloudy.

clear sky- light winds- water perception I chose 2 only because of the little stuff floating around but could probably say #1 beautiful- couldn't be any nicer. With the rains we keep getting- quality is staying very nice.
mostly sunny- light breeze- beautiful day!
light winds- mostly sunny around 70 degrees
variable winds 5 to 8... 60 degrees... clear sky

column1: I still feel the water is more clear than murky but it is getting closer to murky looking.

column2: Mostly sunny- WNW winds approx 5-7 mph

sunny and light winds- one loon swimming nearby! Have seen 3 momma mallards- one with 3- one with 5 and one with 7 babies that are growing up fast!! Had 3 families of geese around the lake also. two weeks ago- we saw a fawn swim across a narrow bay and get up shakily out of the water!
partly cloudy and hot- inch of rain last night

column1: I marked water perception as 1- it was closer to one than two......

column2: Clear sky- light breeze. Start of some blue green algae in some shallow areas but otherwise still real good and rain expected tomorrow.  Our resident eagles had 2 babies this year and they are growing up fast!
Sunny clear skies- winds from ssw the computer says but seemed more westerly to me.5- 7 mph w/ little gusts.
calm and sunny. Last couple days and nights were cold!
clear sky and very light breeze.
mostly sunny. windy but no white caps.
light breeze- partly cloudy. 46 degrees early morning.

clear sunny skies- very light breeze. loon calling. new set of 5 baby mallards. Putting the water appearance as clear because it isn't totally murky. Looks brown probably from all the run off from the heavy rains.
over cast and light breeze with light rain over night. Heard one loon
mostly sunny and calm. water looking much better than a month ago.
Overcast. Bad storms day before. Had a loon fishing near me while taking the water temp.
mostly clear and very calm- beautiful morning.
partly cloudy- slight breeze. Algae bloom started about a week ago and took a hold over the week end. Saw one loon on the way to the deep hole.
The whole lake is green. mostly cloudy with a slight breeze.

Light breeze with occasional gusts. Mostly Cloudy. After 3 cold nights and an 1 1/2 inches of rain yesterday- the water is still green but looks better. Could see 3 ft on the secchi disc when last week just over 2 ft.
overcast- light to variable winds. Lake is still very green and yucky looking.
Mostly sunny- light breeze. Heard two loons calling. Water has improved.
mild chop on water. Still have a momma loon feeding her offspring.
mostly cloudy with light breeze with some gusts.Water is mainly clear with a bit of pollen. Water higher than 2017.

column1: Seems like the ducks and geese did not have as many babies as last year.

column2: Partly cloudy- light breeze. Lake is very high. surprised clarity with secchi was only 11.5. I did test 3 times. Water is looking between 1 to 2 for perception as there is some pollen going on (from pines??) I haven't seen any loon babies. Two geese families but not a lot of babies. One mallard family with 6 babies. I normally have lots of sunfish at my dock but not this year. Because of high water???
partly sunny- light winds- water looks a bit brown out at the deep hole but would still consider it blue for the most part.

light breeze- mostly sunny beautiful day! Heard a loon call. The past week enjoyed watching a mom and dad loon feed their baby that is getting bigger! Saw a newer hatch of mallards. Also enjoyed a mallard family of 3 babies that seem to grow a lot each day. They like to come rest and feed by my Mom's cabin. Plus a friendly doe that comes by our cabin munching of foliage. Luckily has left my impatiens alone so far this year!!
calm and mostly sunny. Parent loons with their baby near by.

mostly sunny with a light breeze. Saw one loon fishing. I gave the perception a 1 even though there was a little- very little algae. Water is wonderful for swimming especially after last years horrible algae bloom.
sunny with west winds 3 to 5 mph. Loon calling in the bay.
lite breeze with a few gusts. mostly clear sky. 71 degrees

column1: perception is between 1 and 2. little more algae looking stuff so gave it a 2.

column2: Loon nesting in bay by Persells. Sunny and calm. Loon swam by at deep hole. Showing Dennis Persells how to do the Lake Monitoring Secchi + Chem
baby loon on Mom's back! overcast light winds

column1: Dennis learning how to do the water test.

column2: Sunny and Calm. Saw a baby and adult loon in Portage Bay. Sunny and calm. Saw adult and baby loon in Portage Bay.
